last_episode_to_air.name: Sphere and Loathing in Outer Space
last_episode_to_air.overview: Milo faces down a cosmic storm made of negative probability ions, while Melissa, Zack, Cavendish, Dakota, Perry, and Doof work their way through the alien populace to save their friend.

name: Milo Murphy's Law
overview: Milo Murphy is the personification of Murphy’s Law where anything that can go wrong will go wrong. Suffering from Extreme Hereditary Murphy’s Law condition (EHML), Milo always looks to make the best of the cards he’s been dealt and his endless optimism and enthusiasm can turn any catastrophe into a wild adventure. Together, he and his friends will learn that it’s all about a positive attitude and not to sweat the big stuff… and it’s all big stuff.

episodes.name: Going the Extra Milo
episodes.overview: Zack, the new kid in town, finds that even a simple trip to school becomes an adventure when he meets Milo Murphy.

episodes.name: Sunny Side Up
episodes.overview: After science teacher Mrs. Murawski announces a science project, Milo, Zack, and Melissa must overcome Murphy's Law to protect an egg and their grades.

episodes.name: Rooting for the Enemy
episodes.overview: Milo is allowed to attend his first school football game since the home team, The Geckos will lose anyway, but discovers a way he can help them win.

episodes.name: The Undergrounders
episodes.overview: While on the subway on a school field trip, Milo’s car gets thrown off course and he, Zack and Melissa discover an underground city of subterranean creatures.

episodes.name: The Doctor Zone Files
episodes.overview: Sara wants to go see The Doctor Zone Files movie with Milo, but worries about potential problems.

episodes.name: The Note
episodes.overview: Milo and the gang spend the entire day chasing after his doctor’s note that excuses an entire semester of absences, illness and shenanigans caused by Murphy’s Law.

episodes.name: Party of Peril
episodes.overview: The other school kids, led by Melissa and Zack, throw a surprise birthday party for Milo at a go-kart arena.

episodes.name: Smooth Opera-tor
episodes.overview: Zack, Melissa, and Milo attend an opera performance with Amanda, but Milo accidentally ends up backstage and attempts to prevent any havoc from occurring.

episodes.name: Worked Day
episodes.overview: It's career day and Milo is having a hard time deciding what his career should be. He tries to decide while visiting the water works, fire department, and hospital. But of course, everything goes wrong. Meanwhile, Dakota and Cavendish try and make sure a truck full of pistachios makes it to the pistachio warehouse.

episodes.name: Wilder West
episodes.overview: Milo and his friends visit a dude ranch. While horse back riding, they meet a girl named Jackie who joins their posse, and Zack is smitten with love. But, Jackie leads them into more danger than usual. Meanwhile, Sara is going crazy because the ranch reminds her of scenes from The Doctor Zone Files, and invites other fans to join in the geek fest.

episodes.name: Family Vacation
episodes.overview: When Milo accidentally joins another family on their vacation, the new family must learn to cope with Murphy’s Law.

episodes.name: Murphy's Lard
episodes.overview: Milo and Zack try to help Melissa overcome her secret fear of roller coasters.

episodes.name: Secrets and Pies
episodes.overview: Milo and Melissa share their most embarrassing stories, but Zack refuses to reveal his past.

episodes.name: Athledecamathalon
episodes.overview: The gang participates in a school event that combines both the academic and athletic decathlon.

episodes.name: The Substitute
episodes.overview: A jaded science substitute teacher, Ms. Baxter, re-discovers her love of teaching after a life-altering day with Milo.

episodes.name: Time Out
episodes.overview: Cavendish and Dakota compete against two of the agency’s top operatives, Brick and Savannah, to impress their boss.

episodes.name: We're Going to the Zoo
episodes.overview: At a donation drive, Milo accidentally gives away his mother's vintage T-shirts. Meanwhile, Cavendish and Dakota are assigned to protect the pistachios at the zoo.

episodes.name: School Dance
episodes.overview: Amanda is concerned that Milo will ruin everything at her carefully orchestrated school dance.

episodes.name: Battle of the Bands
episodes.overview: Milo, Melissa, Zack, and Mort's band enters the battle of the bands, where Zack discovers his old boy band is competing.

episodes.name: The Math Book
episodes.overview: Milo, Zack and Melissa go to school after sunset to retrieve Melissa's math book. Unfortunately, she leaves the spare key inside the locked classroom, so the three go on a "quest" in search of the mysterious janitor, otherwise known as the "key-keeper".

episodes.name: The Little Engine That Couldn't
episodes.overview: When Melissa’s dad drives her and Milo into town on a decommissioned old fire engine, chaos ensues.

episodes.name: The Llama Incident
episodes.overview: Milo and Melissa finally tell Zack the story of the infamous Llama Incident.

episodes.name: Missing Milo
episodes.overview: When Cavendish and Dakota stop Milo from destroying a pistachio plant, they change the future. Pistachio plants become sentient and take over the planet, so Cavendish, Dakota and Milo must race through time to save the future.

episodes.name: Star Struck
episodes.overview: Milo wants to get an autograph from his favorite actor, Tobias Toopanen, who is shooting a film in town.

episodes.name: Disaster of My Dreams
episodes.overview: Elliot Decker is hired as the school’s head safety monitor.

episodes.name: A Clockwork Origin
episodes.overview: Milo, Zack and Melissa set out in search of a missing robot that previously escaped.

episodes.name: Perchance to Sleepwalk
episodes.overview: Milo begins to sleepwalk through some nearby woods. Meanwhile, Cavendish and Dakota have a "ditch day" from pistachio duties after their ordeal with the Pistachions.

episodes.name: Some Like It Yacht
episodes.overview: The students take a trip on the school yacht.

episodes.name: Backward to School Night
episodes.overview: Parents become children at Back to School Night.

episodes.name: World Without Milo
episodes.overview: Elliot gets to see what the world would be like without Milo.

episodes.name: The Race
episodes.overview: Milo runs a race as Cavendish and Dakota gets stuck in the Old West.

episodes.name: LoveTogboggan
episodes.overview: With Milo away skiing, Sara finally feels safe enough to go on a date.

episodes.name: The Island of Lost Dakotas
episodes.overview: Dakota travels back in time to save Cavendish.

episodes.name: Fungus Among Us
episodes.overview: Milo, Cavendish, and Dakota travel back to 1965 and inspire the creation of Dr. Zone only to encounter a sinister plot to take over the world.

episodes.name: Milo's Halloween Scream-A-Torium!
episodes.overview: Zack doesn’t think anything about Halloween can scare him anymore, but he didn’t account for Murphy’s Law.

episodes.name: A Christmas Peril
episodes.overview: Milo surprises his parents by inviting the extended Murphy family to town for Christmas, multiplying the effects of Murphy’s Law.

episodes.name: The Phineas and Ferb Effect
episodes.overview: Milo, Zack, and Melissa—with help from Phineas, Ferb, Candace, Buford, and Baljeet—help conquer Murphy's law to stop a swarm of Pistachions.

episodes.name: Snow Way Out
episodes.overview: In a similar vein as "Going the Extra Milo", Milo and Zack attempt to survive Murphy's Law while getting to school on a cold winter day while Bradley and Melissa bet on whether they'll make it on time again. Meanwhile, Cavendish and Dakota are forced to stand before the Time Council for their constant failures, resulting in their being fired and having their ability to time travel revoked.

episodes.name: Teacher Feature
episodes.overview: After Scott the Undergrounder and Mrs. Murawski appear to hit it off and set up a date, Milo and the gang attempt to help the former look more presentable and normal.

episodes.name: Picture Day
episodes.overview: Melissa and Zack become determined to get a good picture of Milo for school Picture Day after learning he's never had a good one due to Murphy's Law; but Chad misinterprets this as Milo being a vampire and recruits Mort to help him prove it. Meanwhile, Cavendish and Dakota get new jobs at P.I.G. (Paranormal Investigation Group) and try to capture a Yeti on camera to impress their new boss.

episodes.name: Agee Ientee Diogee
episodes.overview: Doofenshmirtz reminisces on an adventure he had with Diogee the previous summer after the canine got caught up in an Agent P style mission.

episodes.name: Game Night
episodes.overview: Milo and his friends and family decide to finally attempt to finish a board game.

episodes.name: Pace Makes Waste
episodes.overview: Milo and Elliot are the pace car drivers for a charity race.

episodes.name: Cake Splosion'
episodes.overview: Milo and Amanda get the chance to be on the latter's favorite TV show, Cake 'Splosion!, an extreme kids' cooking show.

episodes.name: Lady Krillers
episodes.overview: Hollywood is rebooting the first Krillhunter movie with all women, so Milo and the gang help Tobias Trollhammer audition as a woman. Meanwhile, Cavendish and Dakota try to catch an alien while picking up trash by the highway.

episodes.name: Doof's Day Out
episodes.overview: Sara starts to go insane from Dr. Doofenshmirtz constantly invading her personal space, so he goes out with the rest of the Murphy family to try new things

episodes.name: Disco Do-Over
episodes.overview: Learning that the local skating rink is closing down, Milo convinces his parents to pursue their dream of winning a disco skating competition they were unable to finish years ago before that happens. Elsewhere, Cavendish and Dakota are assigned to pick up seemingly ordinary lawn gnomes from a little old lady.

episodes.name: The Ticking Clock
episodes.overview: Milo and his friends try to save the old clock at City Hall that Melissa's great-grandmother designed. Meanwhile, Doof tries to help the city by removing sidewalk gum under Agent P's supervision.

episodes.name: Managing Murphy’s Law
episodes.overview: Amanda helps Milo, Zack, Melissa, and Mort prepare for an afternoon concert while aliens try to covertly study Milo. Elsewhere, Cavendish and Dakota find themselves losing time and not remembering why.

episodes.name: Milo’s Shadow
episodes.overview: Doof shadows Milo to see how he navigates around Murphy's Law. Meanwhile, Cavendish joins an extraterrestrial conspiracy support group.

episodes.name: Sick Day
episodes.overview: While Milo is sick, two shapeshifting aliens attempt to get a tissue sample. Meanwhile, under Monogram's orders, Agent P continues to keep Doof from doing harm while attempting to do good.

episodes.name: Field of Screams
episodes.overview: When his Uncle Cornelius asks for help on his farm, Zack seeks out to prove to a doubtful Milo and Melissa that a "city boy" like him can handle the job. Meanwhile, on a nearby farm, Cavendish and Dakota are assigned to pick up a fallen UFO piece from a farmer who wants to become famous in the tabloids.

episodes.name: Spy Little Sister!
episodes.overview: While heading to a mentor program she doesn't want to be a part of, Melissa ends up paired with Savannah on a mission to stop a rampaging robot that Milo and Zack accidentally built at the science fair before it destroys half of Danville.

episodes.name: Dog Walker, Runner, Screamer
episodes.overview: Elliott gets hurt because of a Murphy's Law related incident, so Milo helps him with his second job as a dog walker. Meanwhile, Cavendish and Dakota discover an alien anti-gravity device and try to show it to Mr. Block for a promotion.

episodes.name: Now I Am a Murphy
episodes.overview: After discovering a boombox in the attic, Milo, Martin, and Grandpa Murphy go camping so Milo can undergo a family rite of passage to become a "Murphy Man". While the men are away, the Murphy women and Doof go to an art museum to celebrate the day without Murphy's Law, but Doof causes chaos in its place.

episodes.name: Freefall
episodes.overview: After an incident with a skydiving simulator, Milo, Melissa, and Zack are left in a cycle of falling and rising through the sky while Diogee tries to save them. Meanwhile, Cavendish and Dakota, while flying a plane and trailing a "Don't Litter Our Planet" banner, accidentally gain rivals in the form of Colonel Niblet and Lieutenant Tenant after taking the blame for Milo and his friends destroying one of their facilities.

episodes.name: Milo's World
episodes.overview: While waiting for Milo to come join them for lunch, Melissa, Zack, Bradley, Mort, Chad, and Sara present "Neil From the Comic Shop" with differing theories on what Milo really is; ranging from him being a wizard, a supervillain, and a robot.

episodes.name: Abducting Murphy's Law
episodes.overview: Milo gets abducted by the recurring alien characters introduced this season, while Melissa, Zack, and Doof attempt to look for him. While on trash duty, Cavendish sees the abduction from a distance, but Dakota does not. This causes a large argument between them, which ultimately ends in the dissolution of their partnership and the former going rogue.

episodes.name: The Goulash Legacy
episodes.overview: Eons in the future, an elderly man tells his grandson how a sentient crockpot of goulash came to be and defeated an army of robot screech owls. Back in the past, Milo, his friends, and Doof attempt to protect Brigette's goulash from Murphy's Law and Doof's hand-held-inators.

episodes.name: The Dog Who Knew Too Much
episodes.overview: After being told to go home again, Diogee crosses paths with Agent P and enemy agents after he swallows a flash drive disguised as a cookie. Meanwhile, Brigette makes Doof and Sara pick up dirty clothes, so the former builds a robot hamper-inator to do the job for them.

episodes.name: Adventure Buddies
episodes.overview: Doof becomes inspired to find an "adventure buddy" to get over Agent P, and winds up joining Scott on a boat ride through the sewers.

episodes.name: Ride Along Little Doggie
episodes.overview: While attending a school award ceremony, Milo attempts to get to the stage in time to collect an award he was nominated for. Meanwhile, Diogee ends up riding along with two of Danville's police officers while they attempt to catch Zippy, the world's fastest koala, and rescue one of their K-9 officers.

episodes.name: Look at this Ship
episodes.overview: Milo attempts to escape his room so he can go out for the day with Zack and Melissa. Elsewhere, Dakota teams up with Doof to find Cavendish, who's attempting to show various news outlets a crashed U.F.O. with a malfunctioning cloaking device.

episodes.name: Cast Party
episodes.overview: After Zack breaks his leg getting tangled in a harp while doing interpretive dance, all of his friends plan a "cast party". At said party, everyone shares stories of how they all broke something without Milo, Martin, or Murphy's Law around; as far as they know.

episodes.name: Safety First
episodes.overview: Milo and Elliot accidentally get handcuffed together. Meanwhile, Zack and Melissa attempt to make a student film, but Doof messes everything up.

episodes.name: Cavendish Unleashed
episodes.overview: Milo, Zack, and Melissa attend a camp to learn new skills. Elsewhere, Cavendish mistakenly unleashes a giant alien.

episodes.name: First Impressions
episodes.overview: Six-year-olds Milo and Melissa meet for the first time, and Murphy's Law makes their first day of 1st grade a big adventure. Meanwhile, Dakota relates to Doof how he first met Cavendish while training to become time agents.

episodes.name: The Speech and Debate League of Death and Destruction Cross Town Explosion Event
episodes.overview: Zack and Milo join Melissa's athletically minded wrestling, speech, and debate team.

episodes.name: The Mid-Afternoon Snack Club
episodes.overview: Milo, Melissa, Zack, Mort, Bradley, and Amanda get in trouble with a substitute teacher and get detention. Meanwhile, the killer cyborg bear from "Now I Am a Murphy" returns to track down Milo and get revenge on him.

episodes.name: Parks and Wreck
episodes.overview: After the school football field is ruined, an event that was meant to be there gets transferred to an old dilapidated park, where Melissa and Amanda compete over who can fix it up faster. Meanwhile, Dakota and Doof deal with an alien device that turns bones into a noodle-like substance.

episodes.name: Escape
episodes.overview: Milo, Lydia, Coach Mitchell, and Scott get stuck in the Googolplex Mall elevator. Meanwhile, Doofenshmirtz and Dakota decide to finally attempt to search for Cavendish with the help of a "Cavenpus" clone made from Cavendish and Agent P's DNA.

episodes.name: Milo in Space
episodes.overview: Continuing from where the previous episode left off, Milo and the gang, now joined by a revived Cavendish, Agent P, and the "Cavenpus", arrive at the grounded UFO; only for Milo to once again be abducted by the same aliens.

episodes.name: Sphere and Loathing in Outer Space
episodes.overview: Milo faces down a cosmic storm made of negative probability ions, while Melissa, Zack, Cavendish, Dakota, Perry, and Doof work their way through the alien populace to save their friend.
